{{!--
  MCP Web Campaign — Related Blog Widget (DESIGN MIRROR ONLY)
  -----------------------------------------------------------
  This file is intentionally a design-only mirror. The MCP Template's
  Clientside Code is a no-op (see related_blog.js) — actual rendering
  is performed by assets/js/mcp-related-renderer.js, which intercepts
  the MCP campaign response and writes cards directly into
  <div id="mcp-related-blog">. Editing this .hbs in the MCP UI does
  NOT affect the live widget; keep it here so designers can reason
  about the markup shape that the renderer mirrors.

  Card data contract (one row in `items`):
    item._id                                 → catalog item ID
    item.attributes.url           (.value)   → href
    item.attributes.name          (.value)   → headline
    item.attributes.publishedDate (.value)   → publish date (Date ms)
    item.dimensions.Topics                   → related Topics items (label = `name`)

  Renders 1–3 blog post cards. The wrapper <aside class="related-articles">
  has CSS that auto-hides when this grid is empty. Cards add the
  .is-blog modifier so the topic chips render in the blog palette.
--}}
{{#if items.length}}
  {{#each items}}
    <a class="related-card is-blog"
       href="{{attributes.url}}"
       data-cy-track="related_blog_click"
       data-cy-target-id="{{_id}}">
      <div class="related-card-meta">
        {{formatDate attributes.publishedDate "DD MMM YYYY"}}
      </div>
      <h4 class="related-card-title">{{attributes.name}}</h4>
      {{#if dimensions.Topics.length}}
        <div class="related-card-topics">
          {{#each dimensions.Topics}}
            <span class="related-card-topic">{{name}}</span>
          {{/each}}
        </div>
      {{/if}}
    </a>
  {{/each}}
{{/if}}
